<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		{>htmlHead/}
		<title>ASQ - Upload new presentation </title>

	</head>
	<body class="no-touch" data-view-name="upload">

		<!--   top menu -->
		{>menu/}

		<!--   Content area   -->
		<div class="container" id="main-container">

			<div class="row">
				<!--   Seperating Headline   -->
				<div class="col-md-12 headline">
					<h2>Upload a file</h2>
				</div>
				
				<div class="col-md-12">
					<p class="upload-gray">Your presentation can be either a zipped filed containing an <a href="http://impress.github.io/impress.js/#/bored" target="_blank">impress.js</a> presentation, or a PDF file.</p>
				</div>

			</div>
			<div class="row" style="padding: 20px 0;">
				<div class="col-md-12">
					<form method="POST" action="/{username}/presentations/" enctype="multipart/form-data" class="form-inline form-upload">

						<div class="input-group">
						    <span class="input-group-btn">
						        <span class="btn btn-default btn-file">
						            Browse&hellip; <input type="file" id="lefile" type="file" name="upload" size="40" maxlength="100000">
						        </span>
						    </span>
						    <input type="text" class="form-control" readonly>
						</div>
						<button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Upload</button>
					</form>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="row" >
				<div class="col-md-12 headline">
					<h2>Upload a zipped HTML presentation with curl</h2>
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-12">
					</p> To zip all the files in the current directory and upload them with curl as a new  presentation:<br>
					<pre class="upload-code-snippet"><code>zip -r - * | curl -i --cookie "{user.cookie}" -F "title=<span class="upload-fa-stack fa-stack fa-lg"> <i class="fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x"></i> <i class="fa fa-stack-1x text">1</i></span>" -F upload=@- {rootUrl}/{user.name}/presentations</code></pre>
					</p>
					
				</div>

				<div class="col-md-12">
					</p> or replace an existing presentation with a zip file:<br>
					<pre class="upload-code-snippet"><code>zip -r - * | curl -X PUT -i --cookie "{user.cookie}" -F "title=<span class="upload-fa-stack fa-stack fa-lg"> <i class="fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x"></i> <i class="fa fa-stack-1x text">1</i></span>" -F upload=@- {rootUrl}/{user.name}/presentations/<span class="upload-fa-stack fa-stack fa-lg"> <i class="fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x"></i> <i class="fa fa-stack-1x text">2</i></span><span class="upload-fa-stack fa-stack fa-lg"> <i class="fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x"></i> <i class="fa fa-stack-1x text">3</i></span></code></pre>
					</p>	
				</div>
				
				<div class="col-md-12">
					<span class="upload-fa-stack fa-stack fa-lg"> <i class="fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x"></i> <i class="fa fa-stack-1x text">1</i></span> The title of the presentation, eg. <code class="upload-inline-code">Introduction to JavaScript</code> <br>
					<span class="upload-fa-stack fa-stack fa-lg"> <i class="fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x"></i> <i class="fa fa-stack-1x text">2</i></span> The id of the presentation, eg. <code class="upload-inline-code">0123456789abcdef01234567</code> <br>
					<span class="upload-fa-stack fa-stack fa-lg"> <i class="fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x"></i> <i class="fa fa-stack-1x text">3</i></span> You can append <code class="upload-inline-code">?preserveSession=true</code> to the URL to preserve the session; good for testing on a live presentation</code>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>

	</body>
</html>